Hartlepool United will not be signing convicted rapist Ched Evans, ‘irrespective of his obvious ability as a football player’.

The League Two club today released a statement  regretting their link with the 25-year-old striker, who was released from prison in October after serving half of a five-year sentence for the rape of a 19-year-old woman in a hotel room in 2011.

However, the club mentioned the appeal in signing a player of Evans’ ability in its statement.

