New manager Ronnie Moore said on Saturday that he would like to bring the Wales international to Victoria Park, but the club backed down in light of strong opposition from supporters and the town’s MP.

The statement read: ‘Following media reports relating to the possible signing of Ched Evans the Club wishes to make its position clear.

‘Hartlepool United do not intend signing Ched Evans and, for the avoidance of doubt, will not be doing so, irrespective of his obvious ability as a football player.

